headline: Nokia stock retreats, follows “excessive” rally tied to Nvidia partnership
summary: Investing.com -- Nokia shares fell 5% in Helsinki on Thursday, paring back gains after a two-day surge of more than 40% driven by excitement over a new partnership with Nvidia. The Finnish telecom equipment maker announced a strategic alliance with the U.S. chip giant focused on AI-powered radio access networks (AI-RAN) and data center networking.
